Feb 2, 2025 > Original Rules </br></br> - Each participant will get a tile in which they are allowed to work. </br> - You can claim a tile to work in just by asking for it, and you'll get put in the queue.

Feb 2, 2025 > Original Rules (2)</br></br> - We'll do the tiles in order of when they are first entered by the player. </br> - You can only work inside the tile you are allocated. </br> - You might be allowed to work on multiple tiles, but if you are, it will be later. For now everyone has 1.

Feb 2, 2025 > Original Rules (3)</br></br> - Your tile's gameplay must be enterable from the previous tile and must end on the edge of an unclaimed tile. If you want to make it so that the gameplay wraps back to previous tiles, you have to get approval from me(ember), and other players may refuse to cooperate if they want.

Feb 2, 2025 > Original Rules (4)</br></br> - Once you claim a tile, you have a time limit of 2 days to show that you have started building, and 1 week to finish.</br> - Once a tile is finished, no one is allowed to add or remove blocks from it.

Feb 2, 2025 > Original Rules (5)</br></br> - If your tile is really bad, all the previous tile creators can take a vote on whether it should be removed. </br> - As of starting this project, there are 9 tiles, and the bottom left tile has been claimed by me.

Feb 2, 2025 > Original Rules (6)</br></br> - If needed, we can add more tiles using the original tile measuring blocks. Don't edit the tile measuring blocks, please. </br> - It would be cool if you added a text box with your name into your tile.

Feb 2, 2025 > Original Rules (7)</br></br> - (Reminder: you don't necessarily have to fill an entire tile with gameplay, as long as you follow the rules above it's acceptable, though I'd like to see some effort of course.)
Feb 2, 2025 > New Rule Editions </br></br> - Participants are now disallowed from adding reachable finish blocks to their tiles.

Feb 2, 2025 > New Rule Editions (2)</br></br> - Whenever they upload a new file to discord, participants are asked to change the name of the file to contain a different number at the end, in order to differentiate the files. (For example: Creation Tiles 3 > Creation Tiles 4)
Feb 16, 2025 > New Rule Editions</br></br> - Participants are now required to verify that their tile is completable before posting it to discord

Feb 16, 2025 > New Rule Editions (2)</br></br> - Participants are now required to move the player back to its original spot in ember’s tile when they are done editing(this rule would be broken countless times after its inception)</br> - The size of the tiles was increased
Mar 9, 2025 > New Rule Editions</br></br> - Participants are now allowed 1 week to show evidence of progress and 2 weeks to finish building.
